This paper deals with object recognition in images, specifically in remote sensing imagery. The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks and auxiliary information to improve recognition accuracy, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of natural language models, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of scientific taxonomy, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of manually annotated attributes, which falls under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
